 receptus by standardization. 9 printed editions are included, among which are 6 of the Textus receptus (incl. the editio princeps of 1555), thus covering the transmission of the Corpus Paulinum from the beginnings up to the 16th century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 0aSyriac languagevTexts. 4aBible. 4aLanguage Studies. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / New Testament.2bisacsh1 aParlevliet-Flesseman, Inetje, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertGorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076710040uhttps://doi.org/10.31826/978146324480440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781463244804423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781463244804/original  a978-3-11-076710-0  Gorgias Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK